files.Title: ToSic.Eav.DataSources.Caching.CacheAllStreams
files.Summary:
Special DataSource which automatically caches everything it's given. It's Used to optimize queries, so that heavier calculations don't need to be repeated if another request with the same signature is used.
Internally it asks all up-stream DataSources what factors would determine their caching. So if part of the supplying DataSources would have a changed parameter (like a different filter), it will still run the full query and cache the results again.

Interface for Dynamic Code with enhancements after v12. It extends

Dynamic Code is the API for files like Razor or WebApis. Supports many properties like App, etc. to ensure that the dynamic code has everything you need.
Also provides many Conversions between and . Important for dynamic code files like Razor or WebApi. Note that there are many overloads to ensure that AsDynamic and AsEntity "just work" even if you give them the original data.

files.Title: ToSic.Sxc.Code.ITypedRazorModel

Object in partial Razor files to access parameters handed in. Example caller:

@Html.Partial(someFile, new { blogPost, file = mainFile, title = "hello" }

Example partial:

var blogPost = MyModel.Item("BlogPost");
var file = MyModel.File("File");
var title = MyModel.String("Title");
Tip

The common data types such as string or have methods to quickly get them in the desired type. This allows things such as var message = MyModel.String("Message"); For less common types you'll need to use and cast it as needed, like this: string message = MyModel.Get("Message");.

files.Title: ToSic.Sxc.WebApi.SecureEndpointAttribute
files.Summary:
Attribute for WebApi controllers, which automatically decrypts encrypted POST payloads for Web API endpoints. Use this attribute on controller or methods to automatically decrypt incoming POST requests.

It will intercepts POST requests with JSON content, checks for encrypted data, and if present, decrypts the payload using the . It then deserializes the decrypted data into the expected parameter type and replaces the action arguments. If the payload is not encrypted, the request content remains unchanged.

See for more information.
ToSic.Sxc is the namespace for 2sxc code.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Documentation.DocumentationPlaceholder
files.Summary: This is a placeholder class, to make sure the namespace is included in the documentation. It is used in namespaces where there are no public classes.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Documentation.InternalApi_DoNotUse_MayChangeWithoutNotice
files.Summary: This attribute serves as metadata for other things to mark them as internal APIs. Use this on objects/properties/methods you want to document publicly for example to improve understanding of the system - but still mark as internal so people are warned

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Documentation.PrivateApi
files.Summary: This attribute marks classes, methods, etc. as private APIs So they should not be publicly documented. By default, all APIs are private, so you only need this attribute on children of classes marked with [PublicApi] see .

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Documentation.PublicApi
files.Summary: This attribute marks classes, properties etc. as public APIs. Any API / code with this attribute will be published in the docs. You can apply it to anything, but usually you will only need it on classes.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Documentation.WorkInProgressApi
files.Summary: This attribute marks APIs to be publicly documented with a clear warning that it's work in progress.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Helpers.GetOnce<TResult>
files.Summary:
Simple helper class to use on object properties which should be generated once.

Important for properties which can also return null, because then checking for null won't work to determine if we already tried to retrieve it.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Locking.NamedLocks
files.Summary: Very simple helper to manage locks - typically for caching or resource intensive generation operations.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Locking.TryLockTryDo
files.Summary: Execute something if a condition is met, but do it within a lock to avoid duplicate runs

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.CodeRef
files.Summary:
Reference to source code. It contains the path to the file, the method name and the line in the code.

This is used to track the exact location in the code where a log was added/created.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.ICanDebug
files.Summary: Trivial interface just to ensure that we have debug on/off consistent

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.ICanDump
files.Summary: Interface to mark classes which can dump their state into the log as a string.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.IHasLog
files.Summary: Objects which can log their activity, and share their log with other objects in the chain to produce extensive internal logging.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.IHasLogExtensions
files.Summary: Extension to objects having a Log, to connect them to parent logs.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.ILog
files.Summary:
A logger with special capabilities. It can take log messages, and chain itself to other loggers.
If chained, it can broadcast the messages to the other loggers from that time forward. Basically this is the backbone of Insights.

To add messages/logs of all kinds you must use null-safe extension methods. It will require you to add the namespace .

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.ILogCall<T>
files.Summary: A mini logger for a function call, which should be closed using a form of Return(...) when the function completes.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.ILogCall
files.Summary:
A log object used to log the activity of a specific function call. It is usually created in the beginning of the call and closed on various return calls or at the end of the function.

Note that most of the methods used to complete a call are extension methods.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.ILogCallExtensions
files.Summary: Extensions for objects which don't need to return a value.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.ILogExtensions
files.Summary: Various extensions for objects to add logs. They are all implemented as extension methods, so that they will not fail even if the log object is null.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.ILogStore
files.Summary: Interface to add s to the log storage.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.ILog_Actions
files.Summary: Extension methods for Actions (functions which don't return a value).

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.ILog_Add
files.Summary: Various extensions for objects to add logs. They are all implemented as extension methods, so that they will not fail even if the log object is null.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Logging.ILog_Properties
files.Summary: Extension methods for property getters and setters.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Security.Permissions.IHasPermissions
files.Summary: Anything that uses can have custom permissions. This interface provides access to the information stored in the custom permissions.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Services.DependenciesBase
files.Summary: Base class for all Dependency helpers on services.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Services.DependenciesEmpty
files.Summary: Empty dependencies object, in rare cases where a constructor might need it.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Services.HelperBase
files.Summary: Main base class for most helpers which don't use Dependency Injection.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Services.HelperRecordBase
files.Summary: Main base record for most helpers which don't use Dependency Injection.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Services.IIsUnknown
files.Summary: Marks un-implemented objects like SiteUnknown etc.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Services.MyServicesBase<T>
files.Summary: Special type of MyServices (dependency helpers). This one is used to extend dependencies of a base classes . They must then still have the original Dependencies to get them.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Services.MyServicesBase
files.Summary:
Base class for all MyServices. These are helper objects to get dependencies for a class. It should be used when the owning-class is expected to be inherited. This is important for inheriting classes to keep a stable constructor.

Can collect all objects which need the log and init that.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Services.ServiceBase<TDependencies>
files.Summary: Base class for any service which expects a Dependencies class

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Services.ServiceBase
files.Summary: Main base class for most services and helpers which have Logs. Also has an API to auto-connect the logs of child-services.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Services.WarnUseOfUnknown<T>
files.Summary: Object which should be used in the DI of Unknown implementations.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Startup.StartupDI
files.Summary: Startup for Dependency Injection.

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Startup.StartupSysCore
files.Summary: Startup registration for all of ToSic.Sys.Core

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Wrappers.IMultiWrapper<T>
files.Summary: Marks items which can be rewrapped multiple times. Important to keep track of the originally wrapped item to ensure equality checks

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Wrappers.IWrapper<T>
files.Summary: This is for any object which does something, but caries with it an original object which is the type of the hosting system (environment)

files.Title: ToSic.Sys.Wrappers.Wrapper<T>
files.Summary: Helper base class for all wrappers
ToSic.Sys is for internal helpers and base classes which are just FYI.
